'''Michael Svoboda''' (born 15 October 1998) is an Austrian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for {{Italian football updater|Venezia}} club [[Venezia F.C.|Venezia]] and the [[Austria national football team|Austria national team]].<ref name=so>{{soccerway|michael-svoboda/446056}}</ref>

==Club career==
On 20 August 2020, Svoboda signed a three-year contract with Italian [[Serie B]] club [[Venezia F.C.|Venezia]].<ref>{{cite press release |publisher=[[Venezia F.C.|Venezia]] |url=https://www.veneziafc.it/news/ufficiale-michael-svoboda-in-arancioneroverde/ |title=Ufficiale: Michael Svoboda in arancioneroverde |date=20 August 2020 |language=Italian}}</ref>

==International career==
Svoboda made his debut for the [[Austria national football team|Austria national team]] on 10 October 2024 in a [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League B|UEFA Nations League]] game against Kazakhstan at the [[Raiffeisen Arena (Linz)|Raiffeisen Arena]]. He substituted [[Gernot Trauner]] in the 62nd minute, as Austria won 4–0.<ref>{{cite web |publisher=ESPN |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/698936/kazakhstan-austria |title=Austria v Kazakhstan game report |date=10 October 2024}}</ref>

